Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.28,0:00:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times have you read \Nin our publications \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.92,0:00:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences whereby someone is praying \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.82,0:00:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to be guided by God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.26,0:00:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,while at the same time \None of our Kingdom proclaimers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.16,0:00:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is praying to be directed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.17,0:00:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to someone with whom they can share \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.23,0:00:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s inspired wisdom? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.50,0:00:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.54,0:00:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,South Africa: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.54,0:00:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A sister begins \Nher auxiliary pioneer service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.21,0:00:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,praying for Jehovah \Nto help her find someone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.21,0:00:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with whom \Nshe can study the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.38,0:00:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The territory \Nincludes the home of a person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.28,0:00:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,who had been very rude \Nto her in the past. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.92,0:00:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Courageously, \Nshe knocks on the door anyway \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.12,0:00:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and discovers \Nthat new tenants live there\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.83,0:00:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,—a mother and daughter \Nwho had been praying \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.43,0:00:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for someone to help them \Nunderstand the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.93,0:00:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, all three were out \Nin service together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.81,0:00:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The angels certainly know \Nhow to work these things out.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.98,0:01:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it reasonable, then, \Nto believe that the angels \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.18,0:01:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,could also play a role in ensuring \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.18,0:01:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that baptized Christians \Nget the information  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.52,0:01:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that they need \Neither to receive or to give? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.99,0:01:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As our text indicates, \NJehovah ‘guides us with his advice.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.53,0:01:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that work? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.73,0:01:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, often we find ourselves \Nin need of wisdom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.10,0:01:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We pray to Jehovah for direction; \Nwe search the Bible; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.77,0:01:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we search our Christian publications; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.11,0:01:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and at times, we ask people \Nwho are already wise for their advice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.78,0:01:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, Insight, Volume 2, \Nunder “wisdom” refers to this as \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.88,0:01:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“a superior and \Ntimesaving way to wisdom.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.49,0:01:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Superior, that is, \Nto experiencing punishment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.62,0:01:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or watching other people \Ngo through it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.86,0:01:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Insight book \Nthen cites Proverbs 22:17. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.20,0:01:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read that together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.50,0:01:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 22:17, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.10,0:02:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.77,0:02:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Incline your ear and listen \Nto the words of the wise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.04,0:02:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“in order to apply your heart \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.68,0:02:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to my knowledge.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.82,0:02:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the “my” \Nin the expression “my knowledge”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.22,0:02:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jehovah is speaking to us \Nthrough the pages of his Word, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.59,0:02:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,indicating that if we listen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.43,0:02:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to counsel from wise people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.63,0:02:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we can, in fact, \Ndetect the wisdom of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.63,0:02:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, \NPsalm 32:8 gives us this promise: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.37,0:02:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will give you insight \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.08,0:02:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“and instruct you \Nin the way you should go. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.98,0:02:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I will give you advice \Nwith my eye upon you.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.95,0:02:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, does that mean \Nthat if we pray intensely, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.29,0:02:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will give us \Ntailor-made counsel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.42,0:02:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,designed to fit \Nour individual circumstances\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.09,0:03:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—that somehow through either \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.13,0:03:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,an encouraging visit \Nby a mature Christian,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.90,0:03:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,, a talk at one of the meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.57,0:03:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or some information \Nin one of our publications, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.40,0:03:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we will find exactly what we need? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.01,0:03:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.11,0:03:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,prayers are often answered \Nin that exact way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.01,0:03:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, with regard to elders’ meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.45,0:03:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers are trained to recognize \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.02,0:03:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that Christ by means of his holy spirit \Ncan influence any elder \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.99,0:03:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,(even the youngest, \Nmost reticent elder on the body) \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.73,0:03:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to make an expression \Nthat results \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.26,0:03:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in wise decisions\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.63,0:03:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,—decisions that may not have been reached \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.44,0:03:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,if each elder \Nhad been consulted individually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.24,0:03:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But, now, does that mean \Nthat every expression \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.71,0:03:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,made by an elder automatically \Nreflects the knowledge of God? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.98,0:03:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to remember \Nthat just as one who desires wisdom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.08,0:03:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,has a responsibility to seek it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.75,0:04:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so likewise one who gives advice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.06,0:04:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,has a responsibility to base his comments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.66,0:04:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,on Jehovah’s inspired Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.66,0:04:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes emotion \Nmay get the better of an adviser. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.50,0:04:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we tell whether \Nthat is taking place? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.97,0:04:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn with me, please, \Nto 1 Samuel chapter 23\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.37,0:04:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—1 Samuel 23. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.61,0:04:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how many times \Ndid King David receive advice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.08,0:04:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,from the likes of Gad, Nathan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.92,0:04:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Abigail, Abishai, others? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.29,0:04:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How did David respond to it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.45,0:04:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, first, please note \Nthat David had the admirable habit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.66,0:04:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of inquiring of Jehovah \Nbefore making decisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.29,0:04:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at what it says here \Nin chapter 23, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.16,0:04:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Samuel 23:2: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.43,0:04:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“So David inquired of Jehovah: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.07,0:04:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Should I go and strike down \Nthese Philistines?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.74,0:04:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah said to David: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.74,0:04:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Go, strike down the Philistines \Nand rescue Keilah.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.51,0:04:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the men of David \Nsaid to him: ‘Look! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.51,0:04:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘We are afraid while here in Judah; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.68,0:05:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘how much more so if we go to Keilah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.95,0:05:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘against the battle line \Nof the Philistines!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.95,0:05:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“So David inquired \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.19,0:05:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,once again of Jehovah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.43,0:05:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And many other texts show \Nthat this was David’s practice.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.46,0:05:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, there were also \Nnotable occasions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.83,0:05:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,when David \Ndid not first inquire of Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.97,0:05:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,such as when he determined \Nto destroy Nabal \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.67,0:05:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and every male in his household, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.68,0:05:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as reported in chapter 25. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.88,0:05:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But David recognized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.91,0:05:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in the words of Abigail \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.38,0:05:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowledge of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.55,0:05:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice what he said \Nat 1 Samuel 25:32, 33: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.26,0:05:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“At this David said to Abigail: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.06,0:05:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Praise Jehovah the God of Israel, \Nwho sent you this day to meet me! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.73,0:05:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘And blessed be your good sense! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.47,0:05:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘May you be blessed \Nfor restraining me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.14,0:05:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘this day from incurring bloodguilt \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.14,0:05:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and from taking revenge \Nwith my own hands.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.57,0:06:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Abigail brought Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.74,0:06:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,back to David’s mind, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.21,0:06:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and he could see \Nthat this was from Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.02,0:06:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, there were other times \Nwhen David’s advisers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.69,0:06:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,were pointing to what \Nthey considered to be proof \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.29,0:06:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s divine intervention, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.29,0:06:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but David did not buy into it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice what it says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.40,0:06:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Samuel 24:4: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.11,0:06:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“David’s men said to him: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.14,0:06:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,, “‘This is the day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.31,0:06:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘on which Jehovah is saying to you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.71,0:06:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“Look! I am giving \Nyour enemy into your hand, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can do to him \Nwhatever seems good to you.”’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.39,0:06:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how would David \Nrespond to that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.86,0:06:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Would he say: “You’re right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.23,0:06:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“Saul tried to kill me three times. \NHe’s been hunting me for years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.60,0:06:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“He’s obviously lost \NJehovah’s holy spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.77,0:06:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“Isn’t that why \NSamuel anointed me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.90,0:07:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“And now, look, \Nhere he is by himself, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“vulnerable, in our very cave. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.41,0:07:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“When does that ever happen? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.64,0:07:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Clearly, Jehovah has given me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.11,0:07:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,this opportunity to seize the kingship.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,David did not draw that conclusion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.95,0:07:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We get a clue \Nin 1 Samuel chapter 26. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.22,0:07:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, once again, \Nthe counsel he receives in verse 8. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.89,0:07:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a coincidence \Nthat David and his men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.73,0:07:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,now find Saul \Nand his army of 3,000 men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.27,0:07:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,totally incapacitated \Nby deep sleep? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.74,0:07:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When does that ever happen? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.97,0:07:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly, that was a gift from God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.44,0:07:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That was what Abishai thought, \Nand so he said in verse 8: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“Today God has surrendered \Nyour enemy into your hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.78,0:07:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“And now, please, \Nlet me pin him to the ground \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.29,0:07:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“with the spear just once, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.46,0:07:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will not need \Nto do it twice.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.26,0:07:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, was that really \Ncounsel from God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.73,0:08:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or just well-intentioned advice \Ndriven by emotion? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.30,0:08:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,David rejected it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.30,0:08:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.10,0:08:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Was he thinking \Nabout Bible principles? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.67,0:08:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Was he thinking \Nabout Leviticus 19:18? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.88,0:08:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You must not take revenge.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.18,0:08:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Likely, as we read what it says \Nin verses 10 and 11, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.78,0:08:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,notice what it says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.79,0:08:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“As surely \Nas Jehovah is living, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.79,0:08:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah himself \Nwill strike him down, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.99,0:08:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“or his day will come \Nand he will die, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.09,0:08:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“or he will go down \Ninto battle and perish. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.73,0:08:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is unthinkable \Nfrom Jehovah’s standpoint for me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.60,0:08:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to lift my hand \Nagainst the anointed of Jehovah!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.57,0:08:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,David loved Jehovah’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.97,0:08:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He tried to consider each situation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.64,0:08:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jehovah’s standpoint. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.51,0:08:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He sought to discern the difference\Nbetween God’s knowledge \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.82,0:08:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and human reasoning.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.02,0:08:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we too may face \Na difficult situation, a decision. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.99,0:09:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone might even encourage us \Nto take action \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.63,0:09:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,without fully considering God’s will. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.73,0:09:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to pray for Jehovah \Nto direct our hearts to his knowledge \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.43,0:09:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,not only that we may receive it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.44,0:09:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but even that we might convey it \Nwhen appropriate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.74,0:09:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you may be the one \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.91,0:09:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,who needs to give \Nthe word of guidance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.74,0:09:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Inquire of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.98,0:09:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure your counsel \Nis in harmony with his Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.78,0:09:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is and if the recipient \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.65,0:09:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,also has a prayerful attitude, \N
